    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka is self-sufficient in groundnuts",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka has become self-sufficient in groundnuts and there is no need to import the variety of cashew required for processing \"jumbo peanuts\", says Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera, the Minister of Agriculture.",
        "The Minister of Agriculture said this while participating in the jumbo groundnut harvesting program at the Middeniya, Thorakolaya government seed farm.",
        "The Ministry of Agriculture stated that although the annual requirement of peanuts in this country is 30,000 metric tons, 64,000 metric tons of peanuts have been harvested so far."
      ],
